OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784227704
OL,3,CMeningitis B jabs should be offered to
OL,4,C15-year-olds on NHS, experts say
OL,6,FThe JCVI recommends that 15-year-olds
OL,7,Fshould either receive two menB jabs if
OL,8,Fthey have never previously been
OL,9,Fvaccinated, or a booster top-up if
OL,10,Fthey received the jab as a baby.
OL,12,FThis applies to children born on or
OL,13,Fafter May 1, 2015, meaning the first
OL,14,Fcohort of students would receive the
OL,15,Fjab in 2030.
OL,17,FThe JCVI said it also "strongly
OL,18,Fsupports" giving two doses of the
OL,19,Fvaccine to children born on or before
OL,20,FApril 30 2015, when they reach 15
OL,21,Fyears old.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784227704
OL,3,CMeningitis B jabs should be offered to
OL,4,C15-year-olds on NHS, experts say
OL,6,FHannah Christensen, Professor in
OL,7,FInfectious Disease Epidemiology at the
OL,8,FUniversity of Bristol, led the
OL,9,Fmodelling of this vaccine and was
OL,10,Fexcited by the findings.
OL,12,FShe said it suggests teenagers will be
OL,13,Fprotected "more efficiently" and that
OL,14,Fa single dose might be enough for
OL,15,Fthose who were vaccinated as an
OL,16,Finfant, changing the "value-for-money
OL,17,Fpicture substantially".
OL,19,FIn addition to this advice, the JCVI
OL,20,Flaunched a one-off summer vaccination
OL,21,Fprogramme for students.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
