CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784227704
OL,3,CMeningitis B jabs should be offered to
OL,4,C15-year-olds on NHS, experts say
OL,6,FDr Shamez Ladhani, consultant
OL,7,Fepidemiologist at the UK Health
OL,8,FSecurity Agency (UKHSA), said that it
OL,9,Fis likely the high number of
OL,10,Fmeningitis cases is due to low
OL,11,Fpopulation immunity.
OL,13,FHe said that over the past 25 years,
OL,14,Fcases of meningitis B have declined.
OL,16,FFewer cases mean less immunity,
OL,17,Fcausing new strains to appear, he
OL,18,Fadded.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
